
'''From the Crowd to the Cloud: Social Media in the Obama Administration'''

Video via http://wilkins.law.harvard.edu/events/luncheons/2009-05-05_losh/2009-05-05_losh.mov


=Description=


Elizabeth Losh, author of [[Virtualpolitik]]: An Electronic History of Government Media-Making in a Time of War, Scandal, Disaster, Miscommunication , and Mistakes, builds on recently published research in this talk about the struggles of government agencies as Internet content-creators, looking at the government’s use of sites like Flickr, YouTube, Facebook, and Twitter."
(http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/interactive/events/luncheons/2009/05/losh)


